This paper deals with unsupervised semantic frame induction using dependency triples extracted from a Web-scale corpus. The paper proposes a graph-based approach, Triframes, to perform triclustering, which is a generalization of clustering for triadic data. The paper also presents replicable benchmarks to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed approach. Given the focus on natural language processing and machine learning techniques, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves graph-based approaches and unsupervised learning, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the use of a Web-scale corpus and replicable benchmarks suggests relevance to sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
